<L>__{exterior down house. day}
<A>__{down the patch and through the open gate with the servants following.}
<C>__{darwin}
<D>__{get aboard. brodie}
<C>__{annie}
<P>__{(shouts back)}
<D>__{mama!}
<A>__{the garden gate clangs shut behind them.}
<L>__{interior down house stairwell upper hallway. the past. day}
<A>__{emma looks out of the upstairs window, realizes they plan to leave without her and hurries downstairs again.}
<L>__{interior coach. the past. day}
<A>__{charles bundles annie inside.}
<C>__{darwin}
<P>__{(to the coachman)}
<D>__{go. go.}
<C>__{emma}
<P>__{(calls)}
<D>__{wait!}
<C>__{darwin}
<D>__{go now!}
<C>__{annie}
<D>__{mama!!}
<A>__{the coach sets off. emma runs to the gate calling desperately.}
<C>__{emma}
<D>__{charles. please god. no. annie!}
<L>__{interior coach. the present}
<A>__{charles, feeble and debilitated, levers himself into the coach with parslow assisting and slumps back in the leather upholstery. servants gather at the gate. some of them tearful, not expecting him to return}
